rsholt who wounded a man, fled to his rectory, and killed one of the men sent to arrest him.The rolls only record the offence and, usually, the outcome. Unfortunately no evidence is recorded so that the whole story is not told.Prepared by BHRS and jointly published with the Historical Manuscripts Commission.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCourt recordszEnglandzBedfordshire. 4aModern History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / 20th Century.2bisacsh  acrimes.  ajustices of the peace.  asessions of the peace.1 aKimball, Elisabeth G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781800107366?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800107366423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800107366/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles